div.p: Depending on the search intention the search is planned in phase two. This planning takes care of cursor-to-page calculations and the optimizations for least requestsÂ by considering search intention details and remote API paging limits. The paging algorithm takes also care of aligned and unaligned page boundaries and the slicing configuration of them.

div.p: The search is structured in three phases. Phase one is the query/search framing, just in a common ActiveRecord compatible way. This is what we call search intention or search settings.

div.p: The client driver package serves a common API to higher levels. While being as abstract as possible its easy to reuse and couple to it. At the moment just the Grape API package is implemented. JSONAPI is going to come soon.

div.p: Last phase (three) is the execution of the search. The details from the paging are used to call the Client Driver as often as planned to fetch the search results. By serving the Ruby Enumarble API it also takes care of the result set slicing as calculated in a stream processing fashion. The Search Executor also handles out-of-data situations transparently and skips further Client API calls. Each found entity comes mapped as an actual instance and is yielded to the search initiation level.
